    <pw:title>
      Deferred Design Decisions
    </pw:title>
    <pw:file-name>
      deferred_design_decisions
    </pw:file-name>
    <pw:body>
      <p>
        In too many programming organizations, every time there's a design debate, nobody ever manages to make a <i>decision</i>, usually for political reasons. So the programmers only work on uncontroversial stuff. As time goes on, all the hard decisions are pushed to the end. <i>These projects are the most likely to fail.</i>
      </p>
